{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":671,"text":"Election night 2008"},{"time":3612,"text":"was a night that tore me in half."},{"time":6971,"text":"It was the night that Barack Obama was elected."},{"time":11360,"text":"[One hundred and forty-three] \nyears after the end of slavery,"},{"time":15733,"text":"and [43] years after the passage"},{"time":18010,"text":"of the Voting Rights Act,"},{"time":19750,"text":"an African-American was elected president."},{"time":23790,"text":"Many of us never thought that this was possible"},{"time":27537,"text":"until the moment that it happened."},{"time":30309,"text":"And in many ways, it was the climax"},{"time":33524,"text":"of the black civil rights movement"},{"time":35330,"text":"in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37388,"text":"I was in California that night,"},{"time":39237,"text":"which was ground zero at the time"},{"time":41123,"text":"for another movement:"},{"time":42947,"text":"the marriage equality movement."},{"time":45940,"text":"Gay marriage was on the ballot"},{"time":47746,"text":"in the form of Proposition 8,"},{"time":50830,"text":"and as the election returns started to come in,"},{"time":54535,"text":"it became clear that the right"},{"time":56651,"text":"for same sex couples to marry,"},{"time":59024,"text":"which had recently been granted\nby the California courts,"},{"time":62076,"text":"was going to be taken away."},{"time":64365,"text":"So on the same night"},{"time":66548,"text":"that Barack Obama won his historic presidency,"},{"time":70830,"text":"the lesbian and gay community suffered"},{"time":73322,"text":"one of our most painful defeats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76600,"text":"And then it got even worse."},{"time":80127,"text":"Pretty much immediately,"},{"time":82121,"text":"African-Americans started to be blamed"},{"time":84567,"text":"for the passage of Proposition 8."},{"time":86899,"text":"This was largely due to an incorrect poll that said"},{"time":90496,"text":"that blacks had voted for the measure"},{"time":92255,"text":"by something like 70 percent."},{"time":94740,"text":"This turned out not to be true,"},{"time":96455,"text":"but this idea of pervasive black homophobia set in,"},{"time":102029,"text":"and was grabbed on by the media."},{"time":105286,"text":"I couldn't tear myself away from the coverage."},{"time":107972,"text":"I listened to some gay commentator say"},{"time":110999,"text":"that the African-American community"},{"time":113388,"text":"was notoriously homophobic,"},{"time":115403,"text":"and now that civil rights had been achieved for us,"},{"time":118677,"text":"we wanted to take away other people's rights."},{"time":120810,"text":"There were even reports of racist epithets"},{"time":123617,"text":"being thrown at some of the participants"},{"time":125534,"text":"of the gay rights rallies"},{"time":127200,"text":"that took place after the election."},{"time":129819,"text":"And on the other side,"},{"time":131810,"text":"some African-Americans dismissed or ignored"},{"time":135631,"text":"homophobia that was indeed real in our community."},{"time":139150,"text":"And others resented this comparison"},{"time":141800,"text":"between gay rights and civil rights,"},{"time":144130,"text":"and once again, the sinking feeling"},{"time":147675,"text":"that two minority groups"},{"time":149694,"text":"of which I'm both a part of"},{"time":152144,"text":"were competing with each other"},{"time":155086,"text":"instead of supporting each other"},{"time":157777,"text":"overwhelmed and, frankly, pissed me off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162303,"text":"Now, I'm a documentary filmmaker,"},{"time":165436,"text":"so after going through my pissed off stage"},{"time":168479,"text":"and yelling at the television and radio,"},{"time":171559,"text":"my next instinct was"},{"time":173849,"text":"to make a movie."},{"time":175928,"text":"And what guided me in making this film was,"},{"time":180280,"text":"how was this happening?"},{"time":182078,"text":"How was it that the gay rights movement"},{"time":185278,"text":"was being pitted against the civil rights movement?"},{"time":188589,"text":"And this wasn't just an abstract question."},{"time":191834,"text":"I'm a beneficiary of both movements,"},{"time":194189,"text":"so this was actually personal."},{"time":197273,"text":"But then something else happened"},{"time":198868,"text":"after that election in 2008."},{"time":201829,"text":"The march towards gay equality"},{"time":204217,"text":"accelerated at a pace"},{"time":206266,"text":"that surprised and shocked everyone,"},{"time":209288,"text":"and is still reshaping our laws and our policies,"},{"time":213910,"text":"our institutions and our entire country."},{"time":216963,"text":"And so it started to become increasingly clear to me"},{"time":220828,"text":"that this pitting of the two movements"},{"time":222926,"text":"against each other actually didn't make sense,"},{"time":226508,"text":"and that they were in fact"},{"time":227740,"text":"much, much more interconnected,"},{"time":231061,"text":"and that, in fact, some of the way"},{"time":233251,"text":"that the gay rights movement has been able"},{"time":235570,"text":"to make such incredible gains so quickly"},{"time":239145,"text":"is that it's used some of the same tactics"},{"time":241193,"text":"and strategies that were first laid down"},{"time":244880,"text":"by the civil rights movement."},{"time":246740,"text":"Let's just look at a few of these strategies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250493,"text":"First off, it's really interesting to see,"},{"time":252772,"text":"to actually visually see, how quick"},{"time":254740,"text":"the gay rights movement has made its gains,"},{"time":256810,"text":"if you look at a few of the major events"},{"time":259996,"text":"on a timeline of both freedom movements."},{"time":263720,"text":"Now, there are tons of milestones"},{"time":267302,"text":"in the civil rights movement,"},{"time":268523,"text":"but the first one we're going to start with"},{"time":270416,"text":"is the 1955 Montgomery bus boycott."},{"time":274312,"text":"This was a protest campaign"},{"time":276900,"text":"against Montgomery, Alabama's segregation"},{"time":279845,"text":"on their public transit system,"},{"time":281852,"text":"and it began when a woman named Rosa Parks"},{"time":284711,"text":"refused to give up her seat to a white person."},{"time":287839,"text":"The campaign lasted a year,"},{"time":290117,"text":"and it galvanized the civil rights movement"},{"time":292216,"text":"like nothing had before it."},{"time":295183,"text":"And I call this strategy the"},{"time":298035,"text":"\"I'm tired of your foot on my neck\" strategy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302962,"text":"So gays and lesbians have been in society"},{"time":307303,"text":"since societies began,"},{"time":309770,"text":"but up until the mid-20th century,"},{"time":312377,"text":"homosexual acts were still illegal in most states."},{"time":316762,"text":"So just 14 years after the Montgomery bus boycott,"},{"time":320872,"text":"a group of LGBT folks took that same strategy."},{"time":325276,"text":"It's known as Stonewall, in 1969,"},{"time":328495,"text":"and it's where a group of LGBT patrons"},{"time":331710,"text":"fought back against police beatings"},{"time":334392,"text":"at a Greenwich Village bar that sparked"},{"time":336348,"text":"three days of rioting."},{"time":338540,"text":"Incidentally, black and latino LGBT folks"},{"time":341266,"text":"were at the forefront of this rebellion,"},{"time":343197,"text":"and it's a really interesting example"},{"time":345466,"text":"of the intersection of our struggles against racism,"},{"time":348677,"text":"homophobia, gender identity and police brutality."},{"time":353370,"text":"After Stonewall happened, gay liberation groups"},{"time":356932,"text":"sprang up all over the country,"},{"time":359271,"text":"and the modern gay rights \nmovement as we know it took off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363891,"text":"So the next moment to look at on the timeline"},{"time":367085,"text":"is the 1963 March on Washington."},{"time":370230,"text":"This was a seminal event\nin the civil rights movement"},{"time":373365,"text":"and it's where African-Americans called for both"},{"time":376113,"text":"civil and economic justice."},{"time":379096,"text":"And it's of course where Martin Luther King"},{"time":381275,"text":"delivered his famous \"I have a dream\" speech,"},{"time":383538,"text":"but what's actually less known"},{"time":385533,"text":"is that this march was organized"},{"time":387868,"text":"by a man named Bayard Rustin."},{"time":391178,"text":"Bayard was an out gay man,"},{"time":393901,"text":"and he's considered one of the most brilliant"},{"time":396533,"text":"strategists of the civil rights movement."},{"time":399450,"text":"He later in his life became a fierce advocate"},{"time":402196,"text":"of LGBT rights as well, and his life"},{"time":405073,"text":"is testament to the intersection of the struggles."},{"time":410150,"text":"The March on Washington"},{"time":411467,"text":"is one of the high points of the movement,"},{"time":413850,"text":"and it's where there was a fervent belief"},{"time":417020,"text":"that African-Americans too"},{"time":419215,"text":"could be a part of American democracy."},{"time":422020,"text":"I call this strategy the"},{"time":423880,"text":"\"We are visible and many in numbers\" strategy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428890,"text":"Some early gay activists were actually"},{"time":431353,"text":"directly inspired by the march,"},{"time":433433,"text":"and some had taken part."},{"time":436639,"text":"Gay pioneer Jack Nichols said,"},{"time":439660,"text":"\"We marched with Martin Luther King,"},{"time":441687,"text":"seven of us from the Mattachine Society\" --"},{"time":444289,"text":"which was an early gay rights organization â€”"},{"time":446740,"text":"\"and from that moment on, we had our own dream"},{"time":450291,"text":"about a gay rights march of similar proportions.\""},{"time":453440,"text":"Several years later, a series of marches took place,"},{"time":457130,"text":"each one gaining the momentum"},{"time":459475,"text":"of the gay freedom struggle."},{"time":461281,"text":"The first one was in 1979,"},{"time":463718,"text":"and the second one took place in 1987."},{"time":468267,"text":"The third one was held in 1993."},{"time":471993,"text":"Almost a million people showed up,"},{"time":475258,"text":"and people were so energized and excited"},{"time":478799,"text":"by what had taken place,"},{"time":479899,"text":"they went back to their own communities"},{"time":482298,"text":"and started their own political"},{"time":483931,"text":"and social organizations,"},{"time":485621,"text":"further increasing the visibility of the movement."},{"time":489512,"text":"The day of that march, October 11,"},{"time":491429,"text":"was then declared National Coming Out Day,"},{"time":494090,"text":"and is still celebrated all over the world."},{"time":496984,"text":"These marches set the groundwork"},{"time":499505,"text":"for the historic changes that we see happening"},{"time":502225,"text":"today in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505073,"text":"And lastly, the \"Loving\" strategy."},{"time":508614,"text":"The name speaks for itself."},{"time":510790,"text":"In 1967, the Supreme Court ruled"},{"time":513603,"text":"in Loving v. Virginia,"},{"time":515492,"text":"and invalidated all laws"},{"time":517612,"text":"that prohibited interracial marriage."},{"time":520845,"text":"This is considered one of the Supreme Court's"},{"time":522760,"text":"landmark civil rights cases."},{"time":526097,"text":"In 1996, President Clinton signed"},{"time":529010,"text":"the Defense of Marriage Act, known as DOMA,"},{"time":532581,"text":"and that made the federal government"},{"time":534920,"text":"only have to recognize marriages"},{"time":537307,"text":"between a man and a woman."},{"time":541276,"text":"In United States v. Windsor,"},{"time":543690,"text":"a 79-year-old lesbian named Edith Windsor"},{"time":546837,"text":"sued the federal government"},{"time":548800,"text":"when she was forced to pay estate taxes"},{"time":551546,"text":"on her deceased wife's property,"},{"time":553048,"text":"something that heterosexual \ncouples don't have to do."},{"time":556365,"text":"And as the case wound its way"},{"time":558674,"text":"through the lower courts,"},{"time":560430,"text":"the Loving case was repeatedly cited as precedent."},{"time":564267,"text":"When it got to the Supreme Court in 2013,"},{"time":566561,"text":"the Supreme Court agreed,"},{"time":568284,"text":"and DOMA was thrown out."},{"time":570737,"text":"It was incredible."},{"time":573131,"text":"But the gay marriage movement"},{"time":574778,"text":"has been making gains for years now."},{"time":578365,"text":"To date, 17 states"},{"time":580930,"text":"have passed laws allowing marriage equality."},{"time":583509,"text":"It's become the de facto battle"},{"time":586187,"text":"for gay equality,"},{"time":588710,"text":"and it seems like daily,"},{"time":590360,"text":"laws prohibiting it are being challenged in the courts,"},{"time":593240,"text":"even in places like Texas and Utah,"},{"time":595827,"text":"which no one saw coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599145,"text":"So a lot has changed"},{"time":601140,"text":"since that night in 2008"},{"time":603402,"text":"when I felt torn in half."},{"time":605860,"text":"I did go on to make that film."},{"time":608210,"text":"It's a documentary film,"},{"time":609887,"text":"and it's called \"The New Black,\""},{"time":611950,"text":"and it looks at how the African-American community"},{"time":614905,"text":"is grappling with the gay rights issue"},{"time":616918,"text":"in light of the gay marriage movement"},{"time":619364,"text":"and this fight over the meaning of civil rights."},{"time":622925,"text":"And I wanted to capture"},{"time":624717,"text":"some of this incredible change that was happening,"},{"time":627798,"text":"and as luck or politics would have it,"},{"time":630890,"text":"another marriage battle started gearing up,"},{"time":633886,"text":"this time in Maryland,"},{"time":635510,"text":"where African-Americans make up 30 percent"},{"time":637997,"text":"of the electorate."},{"time":639199,"text":"So this tension between gay rights"},{"time":642265,"text":"and civil rights started to bubble up once again,"},{"time":646229,"text":"and I was lucky enough to capture"},{"time":648292,"text":"how some people were making the connection"},{"time":651702,"text":"between the movements this time."},{"time":654780,"text":"This is a clip of Karess Taylor-Hughes"},{"time":657378,"text":"and Samantha Masters, two characters in the film,"},{"time":660632,"text":"as they hit the streets of Baltimore"},{"time":663220,"text":"and try to convince potential voters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665557,"text":"(Video) Samantha Masters: That's what's up,\nman, this is a righteous man over here."},{"time":669625,"text":"Okay, are you registered to vote?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671910,"text":"Man: No.\nKaress Taylor-Hughes: Okay. How old are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":673090,"text":"Man: 21.\nKTH: 21? You gotta get registered to vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674901,"text":"We got to get you registered to vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676691,"text":"Man: I ain't voting on no gay shit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679007,"text":"SM: Okay, why? What's up?\nMan: I ain't with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682041,"text":"SM: That's not cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683350,"text":"Man: What made you be gay?\nSM: So what made you be straight?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":688362,"text":"So what made you be straight?"},{"time":693175,"text":"Man 2: You can't answer that question. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":697322,"text":"KSM: I used to not have the same rights as you,"},{"time":699050,"text":"but I know that because a black man like yourself"},{"time":701304,"text":"stood up for a woman like me,"},{"time":702723,"text":"I know that I've got the same opportunities."},{"time":704532,"text":"So you, as a black man, have the opportunity"},{"time":706408,"text":"to stand up for somebody else."},{"time":707720,"text":"Whether you're gay or not,"},{"time":708919,"text":"these are your brothers and sisters out here,"},{"time":710400,"text":"and they need you to represent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711608,"text":"Man 2: Who is you to tell somebody"},{"time":713380,"text":"who they can't have sex with,"},{"time":715000,"text":"who they can't be with?"},{"time":716325,"text":"They ain't got that power."},{"time":718224,"text":"Nobody has that power to say,\nyou can't marry that young lady."},{"time":720892,"text":"Who has that power? Nobody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722696,"text":"SM: But you know what?"},{"time":723743,"text":"Our state has put the power in your hands,"},{"time":725853,"text":"and so what we need you to do"},{"time":727430,"text":"is vote for, you gonna vote for 6."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729910,"text":"Man 2: I got you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731495,"text":"SM: Vote for 6, okay?\nMan 2: I got you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733409,"text":"KSM: All right, do y'all need\ncommunity service hours?"},{"time":735563,"text":"You do? All right, you can always volunteer with us"},{"time":737487,"text":"to get community service hours."},{"time":738918,"text":"Y'all want to do that?"},{"time":740244,"text":"We feed you. We bring you pizza."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742982,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745672,"text":"Yoruba Richen: Thank you."},{"time":748940,"text":"What's amazing to me about that clip"},{"time":750998,"text":"that we just captured as we were filming"},{"time":754392,"text":"is, it really shows how Karess"},{"time":757160,"text":"understands the history\nof the civil rights movement,"},{"time":760328,"text":"but she's not restricted by it."},{"time":762494,"text":"She doesn't just limit it to black people."},{"time":764797,"text":"She sees it as a blueprint"},{"time":766857,"text":"for expanding rights to gays and lesbians."},{"time":770461,"text":"Maybe because she's younger, she's like 25,"},{"time":773390,"text":"she's able to do this a little bit more easily,"},{"time":775648,"text":"but the fact is that Maryland voters"},{"time":778787,"text":"did pass that marriage equality amendment,"},{"time":781913,"text":"and in fact it was the first time"},{"time":784333,"text":"that marriage equality was directly voted on"},{"time":787212,"text":"and passed by the voters."},{"time":789581,"text":"African-Americans supported it at a higher level"},{"time":792545,"text":"than had ever been recorded."},{"time":793731,"text":"It was a complete turnaround from that night"},{"time":796720,"text":"in 2008 when Proposition 8 was passed."},{"time":801074,"text":"It was, and feels, monumental."},{"time":804874,"text":"We in the LGBT community have gone"},{"time":808108,"text":"from being a pathologized and reviled"},{"time":812055,"text":"and criminalized group"},{"time":813859,"text":"to being seen as part of the great human quest"},{"time":818166,"text":"for dignity and equality."},{"time":820890,"text":"We've gone from having to hide our sexuality"},{"time":824767,"text":"in order to maintain our jobs and our families"},{"time":827381,"text":"to literally getting a place at the table"},{"time":830236,"text":"with the president"},{"time":831520,"text":"and a shout out at his second inauguration."},{"time":834646,"text":"I just want to read what he said"},{"time":836207,"text":"at that inauguration:"},{"time":838169,"text":"\"We the people declare today"},{"time":840489,"text":"that the most evident of truths,"},{"time":843525,"text":"that all of us are created equal."},{"time":846579,"text":"It is the star that guides us still,"},{"time":849059,"text":"just as it guided our forebears"},{"time":851285,"text":"through Seneca Falls"},{"time":852799,"text":"and Selma and Stonewall.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":857220,"text":"Now we know that everything is not perfect,"},{"time":861057,"text":"especially when you look at what's happening"},{"time":862970,"text":"with the LGBT rights issue internationally,"},{"time":865953,"text":"but it says something about how far we've come"},{"time":869504,"text":"when our president puts the gay freedom struggle"},{"time":872908,"text":"in the context of the other great freedom struggles"},{"time":874893,"text":"of our time: the women's rights movement"},{"time":877260,"text":"and the civil rights movement."},{"time":879556,"text":"His statement demonstrates not only"},{"time":881899,"text":"the interconnectedness of those movements,"},{"time":884571,"text":"but how each one borrowed"},{"time":886819,"text":"and was inspired by the other."},{"time":890084,"text":"So just as Martin Luther King"},{"time":892832,"text":"learned from and borrowed from Gandhi's tactics"},{"time":895892,"text":"of civil disobedience and nonviolence,"},{"time":898131,"text":"which became a bedrock of\nthe civil rights movement,"},{"time":901230,"text":"the gay rights movement saw what worked"},{"time":904238,"text":"in the civil rights movement,"},{"time":905730,"text":"and they used some of those same strategies"},{"time":907959,"text":"and tactics to make gains"},{"time":909875,"text":"at an even quicker pace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912910,"text":"Maybe one more other reason"},{"time":914997,"text":"for the relative quick progress"},{"time":916792,"text":"of the gay rights movement."},{"time":918967,"text":"Whereas a lot of us continue to still live"},{"time":921847,"text":"in racially segregated spaces,"},{"time":924516,"text":"LGBT folks, we are everywhere."},{"time":927326,"text":"We are in urban communities"},{"time":929589,"text":"and rural communities,"},{"time":931072,"text":"communities of color, immigrant communities,"},{"time":933533,"text":"churches and mosques and synagogues."},{"time":937097,"text":"We are your mothers and brothers"},{"time":940248,"text":"and sisters and sons."},{"time":943056,"text":"And when someone that you love"},{"time":945682,"text":"or a family member comes out,"},{"time":947562,"text":"it may be easier to support their quest for equality."},{"time":952066,"text":"And in fact, the gay rights movement"},{"time":954245,"text":"asks us to support justice and equality"},{"time":956920,"text":"from a space of love."},{"time":959423,"text":"That may be the biggest, greatest gift"},{"time":961883,"text":"that the movement has given us."},{"time":963738,"text":"It calls on us to access that which is most universal"},{"time":968821,"text":"and most intimate:"},{"time":970733,"text":"a love of our brother and our sister"},{"time":973470,"text":"and our neighbor."},{"time":975395,"text":"I just want to end with a quote"},{"time":978198,"text":"by one of our greatest freedom fighters"},{"time":980332,"text":"who's no longer with us, Nelson Mandela"},{"time":983100,"text":"of South Africa."},{"time":984403,"text":"Nelson Mandela led South Africa"},{"time":987304,"text":"after the dark and brutal days of Apartheid,"},{"time":990664,"text":"and out of the ashes of that \nlegalized racial discrimination,"},{"time":995399,"text":"he led South Africa to become the first country"},{"time":998363,"text":"in the world to ban discrimination"},{"time":1001472,"text":"based on sexual orientation within its constitution."},{"time":1005626,"text":"Mandela said,"},{"time":1008281,"text":"\"For to be free is not merely to cast off one's chains,"},{"time":1013207,"text":"but to live in a way that respects"},{"time":1016150,"text":"and enhances the freedom of others.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019399,"text":"So as these movements continue on,"},{"time":1024077,"text":"and as freedom struggles\naround the world continue on,"},{"time":1027038,"text":"let's remember that not only are they interconnected,"},{"time":1030698,"text":"but they must support and enhance each other"},{"time":1034589,"text":"for us to be truly victorious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037873,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039848,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}